 school left after completion of the internship Demonstrated curriculum & learning program development and/or software engineering experience through previous internships, work experience, coding competitions, and/or publications Ease with public speaking and presenting to technical and non-technical audiences Experience creating data-driven reports to share results and recommendations with senior leadership An entrepreneurial attitude; you\u2019ll be developing security training programs that are the first of their kind at Uber, including ongoing education programs for Uber\u2019s engineers focused on secure software development A desire to be part of a team that delivers impactful results every day Excellent interpersonal skills and the ability to communicate effectively with internal and external partners An innate desire to deliver and a strong sense of accountability for your work Organized, self-driven and comfortable in a fast-paced environment Bonus Points For Event management experience Experience scaling a training program to meet the needs of a large organization with an engineering-driven culture Experience in information security clubs/organizations (for instance, collegiate collegiate cyber defense or Capture the Flag competitions, White Hat clubs/organizations, etc.) "
